theorem Topology.interiorClosure_iter7_idempotent
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior
      (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure A)))))))))) =
      interior (closure A) := by
  -- Let `B` be the five-fold iterate.
  set B : Set X :=
      interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure A))))))) with hBdef
  -- Apply the basic idempotence lemma once more.
  have h₁ :
      interior (closure (interior (closure B))) = interior (closure B) :=
    Topology.interiorClosure_idempotent (A := B)
  -- The six-fold iterate collapses to `interior (closure A)` by the previous lemma.
  have h₂ : interior (closure B) = interior (closure A) := by
    simpa [hBdef] using
      Topology.interiorClosure_iter6_idempotent (A := A)
  -- Combine the two equalities.
  simpa [hBdef, h₂] using h₁

theorem Topology.P3_interiorClosureClosure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P3 (interior (closure (closure (A : Set X)))) := by
  simpa [closure_closure] using
    (Topology.P3_interiorClosure (A := A))
